quran[12]{c,v,t}:
  19,65,"the Lord of the heavens and the earth and whatever lies between them. So, worship Him and persevere in His worship. Do you know any one worthy of His name?""
  19,66,"And man says, "Is it that, once I die, I shall be brought forth alive?""
  19,67,"Does not the man remember that We created him before when he was nothing?"
  19,68,"So, by your Lord, We will definitely gather them together with the devils, then We will definitely make them present around the Jahannam, fallen on their knees."
  19,69,"Then We will certainly draw out, from every group, those who are more rebellious against the Rahman (All-Merciful)."
  19,70,"Then of course, We are most aware of those who are more deserving to enter it (the Jahannam)."
  19,71,"And there is none among you who is not to arrive at it. This, on the part of your Lord, is a matter finally decided, bound to happen."
  19,72,"Then We will save those who feared Allah, and will leave the wrongdoers in it, fallen on their knees."
  19,73,"And when Our verses are recited to them in all their clarity, those who disbelieve say to those who believe, "Which of the two groups is superior in respect of its place and better in respect of its assembly?""
  19,74,"And how many a generation We have destroyed before them who were better in assets and outlook!"
  19,75,"Say, "Whoever stays straying, let his term be extended by The Rahman (All-Merciful) still longer until when they will see what they are being warned of: either the punishment or the Hour (of doom), then they will know who was worse in respect of his place and weaker in respect of his forces."
  19,76,"And Allah makes those on the right path excel in guidance. And the everlasting virtues are better with your Lord in respect of reward and better in their return."